Shortbread Crust (Pate Sablee)
  --Tyler Atwell

1 c + 1 tbsp room temp butter
1 1/23 c confectioners' sugar
1/2c almond flour
1/2 tsp kosher salt
2 eggs
3 1/4 c ap flour

In a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream the butter, sugar, almond flour, and salt on medium speed until well incorporated and creamy. Add the eggs slowly, one at a time, mixing until combine after each addition. Add the flour and mix until the flour is no longer visible, being careful to not overmix. Remove from mixer. Shape the dough into a rectangle and wrap with plastic wrap. chill the dough for at least 1 hr before rolling out. Preheat oven to 350F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Roll the dough to a 1/4" thickness, then place in the refrigerator again for 15 min, or until it firms up. Cut into desired shape, place on prepared sheet an inch apart and bake for 18-20 min or until lightly brown around the edges. 

Makes 30-40 cookies (~2lbs dough)
